.TH SYSTUI 1 "2026" "systui" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
systui \- fast, agentless TUI for Linux server administration
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B systui
[\fIGLOBAL OPTIONS\fR] [\fICOMMAND\fR] [\fIARGS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B systui
is a terminal user interface for inspecting and safely operating Linux servers,
locally or over SSH. It detects, explains and correlates system, service, log,
network, docker, cron, security, certificate, database and policy state, and
mediates every change through a confirmation/backup/audit safety engine. It is
agentless (nothing is installed on the remote host) and read-only by default.
.PP
With no subcommand,
.B systui
opens the Hosts grid \(em the local machine plus the SSH inventory \(em from which
you drill into a single host.
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-read\-only
Force read-only mode: never modify the host, regardless of other settings.
.TP
.BR \-\-config " " \fIFILE\fR
Use an alternate configuration file instead of the default location.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print help.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Print version.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B local
Inspect the local machine. This is the default when no subcommand is given.
.TP
.B ssh \fITARGET\fR
Connect to a remote host over SSH.
.I TARGET
is a
.RI \(lq user@host \(rq
or a host id from the inventory. Host-key verification and authentication are
delegated to the system ssh client (known_hosts, ~/.ssh/config, ssh-agent).
.TP
.B fleet \fR[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
Operate on a fleet of inventory hosts (inspection only). Options:
.RS
.TP
.BR \-\-tag " " \fITAG\fR
Restrict to hosts carrying this tag. Repeat for "any of".
.TP
.BR \-\-favorites
Restrict to hosts flagged as favorites.
.TP
.BR \-\-search " " \fITERM\fR
List hosts whose services or ports match TERM, then exit.
.TP
.BR \-\-compare " " \fIA\ B\fR
Compare two inventory hosts side by side.
.TP
.BR \-\-format " " \fIFORMAT\fR
Render a fleet report instead of the overview: markdown, json or html.
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output " " \fIFILE\fR
Write the fleet report to a file instead of stdout.
.RE
.TP
.B report \fR[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
Generate a report of a host's state (local, or remote with \fB\-\-host\fR). Options:
.RS
.TP
.BR \-\-host " " \fIHOST\fR
Host to report on: an inventory id or user@host. Omit for local.
.TP
.BR \-\-format " " \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format: markdown (default), json or html.
.TP
.BR \-\-security
Produce a security-focused report.
.TP
.BR \-o ", " \-\-output " " \fIFILE\fR
Write the report to a file instead of stdout.
.TP
.BR \-\-note " " \fITEXT\fR
Add a review note to the report (may be repeated).
.RE
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B SYSTUI_LOG
Log verbosity to stderr (e.g. \fBdebug\fR, \fBinfo\fR, \fBwarn\fR). Defaults to \fBwarn\fR.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns 0 on success and non-zero on error.
.SH SEE ALSO
Project home: https://github.com/njuante/Systools
.SH AUTHOR
njuante
